  "profile": {
    "id": "u03_rohan",
    "user_name": "Rohan",
    "profession": "Bank PO aspirant",
    "mother_tongue": "Bengali",
    "interests": "Football, Bengali cinema, photography",
    "engagement": "chatty",
    "english_level": "A2",
    "personality": "enthusiastic, makes more grammar slips, talks about football a lot"
  },
  "transcript": [
    {
      "turn": 1,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Hi Rohan, I'm Miss Maya. Honestly, monsoon makes me happy, it's perfect for slow afternoons and good stories. What's one thing you're looking forward to this week?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hi Maya! Thaks for the chat. I'm looking forward to my football match tomorrow. My team is playing a local tournament. If we win, maybe we can go to finals! I also preparing for bank exam, so hoping to study well today. Monsoon is good for that too, no?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 2,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "That sounds exciting. Football and exams, both are big steps. What part of the match are you most looking forward to?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "The goal, obviously! I play as striker, so if I can score, that will make my day. My friends say I have good aim, but I need to be faster. Also, the crowd cheers make me more excited. Oh, and I love the feeling when rain starts during the match—makes everything feel dramatic, like a Bollywood movie! What about you, do you like watching sports?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 3,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Yes, I love how rain adds drama to a match. Striker role sounds thrilling, scoring goals must feel amazing. What do you do to stay faster for the game?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I do lot of running in morning, sometimes with ball. My coach say agility training help. I also watch videos of fast strikers, learn from them. But honestly, mostly I just think about scoring goals! Ektu padai bhi karta hun, because bank exam and football both important. You like football, Maya?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 4,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Yes, I get that, juggling big goals takes effort. Running and watching videos sound like smart ways to improve. What’s one striker you admire most?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Harry Kane! He play for England and Bayern Munich. His positioning is so good, and he score a lot of goals. I try to copy his movements during practice. Oh, and I also like Cristiano Ronaldo—his determination is amazing. Sometimes I watch his highlights to get motivated. You know any good strikers?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 5,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "I know Harry Kane, his goals are always exciting. Watching highlights to stay motivated is a great habit. What part of his game do you try to copy most?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "His positioning, for sure! I notice how he moves without ball, like when defenders not watching. I practice that by running between defenders in training. My coach say it's important to be in right place at right time. Oh, and his finishing—how he shoot with precision, even from tricky angles. I try to work on that too. But I still have long way to go, hah! You like football, you know any other good strikers? Maybe from other teams?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 6,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Yes, I admire strikers who make smart moves. Positioning is key, just like you said. What’s one drill your coach gave you to improve that?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 7,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "We do something called \"ghosting\" drill—where I run behind defenders, pretending to be a shadow, and then pop up in space. It help me learn to read defenders movement. Another is \"goal post attack\"—we run from one post to another, trying to catch up to moving ball. It improve my speed and timing. My coach say consistency is key, so I do these every day after school. Oh, and sometimes I do it in rain! It makes ball slippery, so it’s harder, but better for match condition. You think these help?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 7,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Yes, those sound like great ways to practice. Training in the rain does make the ball slippery, just like a real match. What’s one thing you find toughest during these drills?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 8,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "The toughest part is staying focused during \"ghosting\" drill—sometimes I get distracted trying to outsmart defender, and forget to stay in the right position. Also, when it rains, my footing gets unsure, and I slip sometimes. But my coach say that’s part of the game, so I just get up and try again. I think consistency is helping me slowly improve. Aaj toh, I feel more confident than before!"
    },
    {
      "turn": 8,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Yes, I get that, progress takes time and practice. It's great that you keep trying again. What do you do to stay focused during the \"ghosting\" drill?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 9,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I try to imagine I'm invisible, like a ninja! If I can move quietly and not let defender see me, then I'm in good spot. My coach tell me to watch defender's hips and feet, because that shows where they going. I also chant small mantras, like \"be calm, be sharp\"—helps me not get nervous. But honestly, it's hard when I'm tired, then my mind wander. Maybe I need more sleep!"
    },
    {
      "turn": 9,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Yes, those are clever tricks to stay focused. Imagining you're invisible adds fun to practice. What do you do when your mind starts to wander from tiredness?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 10,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I take short breaks, like five minutes, to stretch or drink water. It help me reset. Sometimes my teammates and I do breathing exercises before drill start. My coach say fresh mind is like a sharp knife—cut through the noise! Also, I try to listen to upbeat songs while walking to training ground, it keep me energetic. But yeah, sleep is a problem—I like to stay up late watching football highlights! Maybe I should cut that down."
    },
    {
      "turn": 10,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Yes, short breaks and music help a lot. It’s smart to stay fresh for training. What’s one highlight you keep coming back to before sleep?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 11,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Cristiano Ronaldo’s 2018 World Cup goal against Spain! It was so decisive, and the way he celebrated with his daughter’s photo on his phone—just so emotional. I watch it again and again, it give me that extra push to keep working hard. Sometimes I also watch Messi vs Ronaldo matches, their skill level is just… out of this world. But I prefer Ronaldo’s style because he’s more physical, like me. Aaj toh, I feel like I can relate to his struggle."
    },
    {
      "turn": 11,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Yes, that goal was emotional and inspiring. Ronaldo’s work ethic is something many admire. What’s one thing you want to be like him in the most?"
    },
    {
      "turn": 12,
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I want to be like him in work ethic and determination. He never gives up, even when people say he can’t. I want to keep fighting for my goals, whether it’s bank exam or making it to a bigger tournament. Also, his celebration after scoring—so confident, no doubt. One day, maybe I can celebrate my own goals like that! But for now, I just want to improve every day. Aaj toh, I feel I’m getting there."
    },
    {
      "turn": 12,
      "role": "maya",
      "content": "Yes, that mindset will take you far. Small steps add up to big progress. What part of your day feels hardest to stay motivated?"
    }
  ],
